Tofu in Garlic Sauce

1 small box of firm tofu, washed and cut into bite-sized cubes
2 tbsp oyster sauce
5 cloves garlic, minced
cornstarch
5 tbsp canola oil
1 tsp sugar
1 tbsp green onions, chopped

Roll each tofu piece in cornstarch to coat.
Heat oil in a pan and fry the tofu pieces until golden brown.Set aside.
Remove excess oil in the same pan except for 1 tbsp and fry garlic until brown.
Add oyster sauce and sugar, give it a little stir.
Then add tofu pieces and stir until each tofu piece is coated by sauce
Sprinkle with chopped green onions before serving.
